    {
      "speaker_id": "sundar-pichai",
      "speaker_name": "Sundar Pichai",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:00:45",
      "text": "Thank you for joining us. Q2 was a strong quarter driven by Search and Cloud momentum. Google Cloud revenue reached $10.4 billion, up 29% year-over-year, and we expect this trajectory to continue into Q3 with Cloud revenue in the range of $10.8 to $11.0 billion. Our AI Overviews feature launched broadly in May and is already showing strong engagement signals that we expect will drive long-term Search revenue growth."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "anat-ashkenazi",
      "speaker_name": "Anat Ashkenazi",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:30",
      "text": "Total revenues were $84.7 billion for Q2, up 14% year-over-year. Operating income was $27.4 billion, reflecting an operating margin of 32%. We continue to invest heavily in AI infrastructure. Capital expenditures were $13.2 billion, and we expect CapEx to remain at elevated levels through the balance of 2024 as we build out our TPU v5 capacity, which we plan to expand by over 200% by year-end."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:35:00",
      "text": "Our first question comes from Eric Sheridan at Goldman Sachs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-eric-sheridan",
      "speaker_name": "Eric Sheridan",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:35:15",
      "text": "Thanks. Sundar, can you talk about what you're seeing in terms of competitive dynamics in the AI assistant space and how Gemini is positioned relative to peers?"
    }
  ],
